Both deliverables are in place.

- `transcript.json` — 25 iterations, 48 hypotheses, 43 analyses; validates against `transcript_schema.json`.
- `analysis_summary.txt` — narrative synthesis covering main effects, interactions, race/insurance disparities, extremes, and supported-vs-refuted hypotheses.

Headline findings: PFS is driven by an 11-feature core (R²≈0.86) — `feature_078` (age-like, +0.18 mo/unit, dominant), `feature_057` (3-level severity, -1.19 mo/level), `feature_051` (-1.35 mo), `feature_038` (+0.97 mo, treatment-like), and several others. Key interactions: `feature_038`'s benefit is abolished by `feature_013`=1 (-1.64 mo) or `feature_043`=1 (-1.45 mo) and amplified by `feature_067`=1 (+0.89 mo). Race (`feature_064`) and insurance (`feature_018`) show no PFS disparity, no differential treatment receipt, and no treatment-effect heterogeneity in any test.
